personalInfo.clubAffl: Sand Hollow GC (St. George, Utah); Coral Canyon GC (Washington, Utah)

tourBios.exmtStatus: Fully Exempt: # Nearest 50 - 15th Web.com Tour qualifier at 2012 PGA TOUR Qualifying Tournament
tourBios.curYearHigh: Earned his first career top-10 in just his second start. After missing the cut at the season-opening Panama Claro Championship, came back with a T7 effort the next week at the Colombia Championship. Strong start was bolstered by a 6-under 65 in the third round, matching the best of the day.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Was all-region in basketball, baseball and golf at Richfield High School in Utah...Was a junior college All-American.
tourBios.personal: Served as Jay Don Blake's caddie when Blake, a fellow Utahn, won the Champions Tour's Songdo IBD Championship in South Korea in 2011...Has worked in retail sales after college...Never travels without sunflower seeds...Favorite college team is BYU...Follows the Utah Jazz and the Oakland A's and Raiders...Dream foursome would include Tiger Woods, Ben Hogan and Bobby Jones...Favorite quote is "Man's reach exceeds his imagination."
tourBios.otherInfo: Played on the National Pro Golf Tour...Took a two-shot lead into the final round of the Utah Open in August after opening 65-65. Shot a final-round 69 at Oakridge CC only to lose to James Drew by two strokes when Drew fired a final-round 64...In early December, was tied for low-professional honors at the Nevada Open in Mesquite. Shot rounds of 68-62-66 to T2 with John Hahn, five shots behind amateur and UNLV golfer Kevin Penner (63-63-65). Split winner's share of $20,100 with Hahn...Has not a made a start on either the PGA TOUR or the Web.com Tour prior to the 2013 season.

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the Web.com Tour was T7th in 2013 at the Colombia Championship.
